QUANTUM 6G SATELLITE NETWORK: COMPREHENSIVE TECHNICAL SPECIFICATIONS

SYSTEM ARCHITECTURE SPECIFICATION

1.0 NETWORK TOPOLOGY

1.1 Constellation Architecture

```
Orbital Configuration:
├─ Layer 1: Quantum Source Layer (600km altitude)
│  ├─ Orbit type: Sun-synchronous polar orbit
│  ├─ Inclination: 97.6°
│  ├─ Planes: 18 orbital planes
│  ├─ Satellites per plane: 12
│  ├─ Total satellites: 216
│  ├─ Phase: 15° separation within plane
│  └─ Revisit time: 10 minutes (any ground station)
│
├─ Layer 2: Quantum Repeater Layer (800km altitude)
│  ├─ Orbit type: Inclined circular orbit
│  ├─ Inclination: 45°
│  ├─ Planes: 12 orbital planes
│  ├─ Satellites per plane: 8
│  ├─ Total satellites: 96
│  ├─ Function: Entanglement swapping nodes
│  └─ Cross-link: 4 optical terminals per satellite
│
├─ Layer 3: User Access Layer (1200km altitude)
│  ├─ Orbit type: Walker constellation
│  ├─ Inclination: 55°
│  ├─ Total satellites: 288
│  ├─ Planes: 24
│  ├─ Satellites per plane: 12
│  └─ Minimum elevation: 30°
│
└─ Special Orbits: 6 satellites in GEO for relay and backup

Total Constellation: 606 active satellites
```

1.2 Ground Segment

```
Quantum Ground Stations (QGS):
├─ Primary Stations: 50
│  ├─ Location: High altitude (>2000m), low turbulence sites
│  ├─ Telescope: 4m diameter Cassegrain
│  ├─ Adaptive optics: 1000-actuator deformable mirror
│  ├─ Quantum detectors: 8× SNSPD arrays
│  ├─ Synchronization: Chip-scale atomic clock (CSAC)
│  └─ Backup: 2× redundant optical systems
│
├─ Metropolitan Nodes: 200
│  ├─ Location: Major city rooftops
│  ├─ Telescope: 1m diameter compact design
│  ├─ Adaptive optics: 200-actuator MEMS mirror
│  ├─ Quantum interface: Fiber coupling to local network
│  └─ Uplink capability: 1550nm laser communication
│
└─ Mobile Terminals: 1000+
  ├─ Type 1: Vehicle-mounted (cars, ships, planes)
  ├─ Type 2: Portable suitcase system
  └─ Type 3: Building-integrated for urban coverage
```

2.0 QUANTUM PHYSICAL LAYER SPECIFICATIONS

2.1 Photon Source Specifications

```
Entangled Photon Source (EPS):
├─ Type: Waveguide Periodically Poled Lithium Niobate (PPLN)
├─ Wavelength: 1550.12nm ± 0.01nm (C-band, ITU channel 35)
├─ Alternative: 810nm for daylight operation (with narrow filtering)
├─ Brightness: 1×10⁹ photon pairs/second/mW (pump at 775nm)
├─ Pair generation rate: 5×10⁷ pairs/second (50mW pump)
├─ Entanglement fidelity: >0.98 (Bell state measurement)
├─ Spectral bandwidth: <100MHz (0.8pm at 1550nm)
├─ Pump laser: 775nm DFB laser, 50mW output, <100kHz linewidth
├─ Temperature stability: ±0.01°C (Peltier controlled)
├─ Polarization extinction ratio: >30dB
├─ Pump suppression: >100dB (double-stage filtering)
└─ Size: 100×80×40mm, mass: 450g

Redundancy: 3× independent sources per satellite
```

2.2 Quantum Memory Specifications

```
Atomic Quantum Memory (AQM):
├─ Type: Rubidium-87 vapor cell with buffer gas
├─ Cell dimensions: 20×20×50mm
├─ Temperature: 65°C ± 0.1°C (controlled by resistive heater)
├─ Magnetic field: 1G ± 0.1mG (3-layer Mu-metal shielding)
├─ Optical depth: >50 (for 795nm transition)
├─ Storage time: 1ms (goal: 10ms with spin echo)
├─ Storage efficiency: >50% (write/read cycle)
├─ Read/write bandwidth: 10MHz
├─ Interface: Telecom to atomic wavelength conversion
├─ Conversion efficiency: >30% (nonlinear crystal or EIT)
├─ Overall system efficiency: >15% (end-to-end)
└─ Coherence preservation: >0.95 fidelity over storage period

Alternative memory: Erbium-doped waveguide for telecom storage
```

2.3 Single-Photon Detector Specifications

```
Superconducting Nanowire Single-Photon Detector (SNSPD):
├─ Material: NbN nanowire on Si substrate
├─ Active area: 20×20μm
├─ Detection efficiency: >85% at 1550nm
├─ Dark count rate: <10 counts/second
├─ Timing jitter: <50ps FWHM
├─ Dead time: <50ns
├─ Recovery time: <100ns
├─ Operating temperature: 2.8K (closed-cycle cryocooler)
├─ Cooler power: 75W input for 1W cooling at 2.8K
├─ Number per terminal: 4 detectors (for polarization analysis)
├─ Redundancy: 2× detector arrays per terminal
└─ Lifetime: >10⁹ detection cycles

Readout electronics:
├─ Amplifier bandwidth: 2GHz
├─ Discriminator threshold: Adjustable in 10μV steps
├─ Time-to-digital converter: 10ps resolution
└─ Data interface: 10Gbps fiber optic to processing unit
```

3.0 OPTICAL COMMUNICATION SPECIFICATIONS

3.1 Transmit Terminal (Satellite)

```
Optical Assembly:
├─ Telescope type: Off-axis Cassegrain
├─ Primary diameter: 150mm
├─ Secondary diameter: 45mm
├─ Effective focal length: 1500mm
├─ Field of view: ±50μrad
├─ Wavefront error: <λ/20 RMS at 1550nm
├─ Pointing accuracy: <0.5μrad RMS
├─ Pointing stability: <0.1μrad over 100ms
├─ Pointing knowledge: <0.05μrad
├─ Optical throughput: >85% (including all elements)
├─ Polarization purity: >100:1
└─ Stray light rejection: >60dB

Transmit Laser System:
├─ Beacon laser: 976nm, 100mW, 10kHz modulation for tracking
├─ Quantum signal laser: 1550nm, pulsed, 100MHz repetition
├─ Pulse width: 100ps FWHM
├─ Extinction ratio: >30dB
├─ Frequency stability: <1MHz/hour
├─ Power stability: <0.1dB/hour
└─ Modulation: Direct modulation or external modulator

Pointing, Acquisition, and Tracking (PAT):
├─ Coarse pointing: Star tracker + reaction wheels, <100μrad
├─ Fine pointing: Fast steering mirror, 2-axis, 1kHz bandwidth
├─ Tracking sensor: Quadrant photodiode, 10MHz bandwidth
├─ Beacon detector: CMOS array, 1000×1000 pixels
├─ Acquisition time: <5 seconds from ±1mrad uncertainty
├─ Handover time: <100ms between satellites
└─ Pointing loss allocation: 3dB maximum
```

3.2 Receive Terminal (Ground)

```
Ground Telescope:
├─ Type: Alt-azimuth mounted Ritchey-Chrétien
├─ Primary diameter: 4000mm
├─ Central obstruction: 1200mm (30%)
├─ Focal ratio: f/8
├─ Field of view: ±100μrad
├─ Mount tracking: 0.1 arcsec RMS
├─ Slew rate: 3°/second in azimuth, 2°/second in elevation
├─ Enclosure: 8m dome with slit opening

Adaptive Optics:
├─ Wavefront sensor: Shack-Hartmann, 20×20 subapertures
├─ Sampling rate: 2kHz
├─ Deformable mirror: 1000 actuators, 2kHz bandwidth
├─ Correction bandwidth: >100Hz (Greenwood frequency)
├─ Strehl ratio: >0.6 at 1550nm (H-V 5/7 seeing)
├─ Tip/tilt correction: Separate fast steering mirror
├─ Reference source: Laser guide star (589nm) or natural star
└─ Control system: FPGA-based, <500μs latency

Atmospheric Compensation:
├─ Scintillation mitigation: Aperture averaging + time averaging
├─ Beam wander correction: Fast steering at 1kHz
├─ Pulse broadening compensation: Deconvolution algorithms
├─ Daytime operation: 0.1nm spectral filter + 100ps time gate
└─ Cloud detection: All-sky camera with ML prediction
```

4.0 QUANTUM PROTOCOL SPECIFICATIONS

4.1 Entanglement Distribution Protocol (QEDP-1)

```
Protocol Stack:
┌─────────────────────────────────┐
│ Application Layer                │
│  - Quantum key distribution      │
│  - Quantum teleportation         │
│  - Distributed quantum computing │
└─────────────────────────────────┘
┌─────────────────────────────────┐
│ Transport Layer (QTP)           │
│  - Entanglement purification     │
│  - Error correction              │
│  - Multiplexing                  │
└─────────────────────────────────┘
┌─────────────────────────────────┐
│ Network Layer (QNP)             │
│  - Routing (Bell state routing)  │
│  - Addressing (Quantum IP)       │
│  - Congestion control            │
└─────────────────────────────────┘
┌─────────────────────────────────┐
│ Link Layer (QLL)                │
│  - Entanglement generation       │
│  - Synchronization               │
│  - Frame structure               │
└─────────────────────────────────┘
┌─────────────────────────────────┐
│ Physical Layer                  │
│  - Photon transmission           │
│  - Detection                     │
│  - Classical communication       │
└─────────────────────────────────┘

Frame Structure:
┌─────────┬─────────┬─────────┬─────────┬─────────┬─────────┐
│ Preamble│ Frame ID│ Source  │ Dest    │ Ent.    │ FEC     │
│ (64 bit)│ (32 bit)│ Addr    │ Addr    │ State   │ (256 bit)│
│         │         │ (48 bit)│ (48 bit)│ (2 bit) │         │
└─────────┴─────────┴─────────┴─────────┴─────────┴─────────┘

Timing Parameters:
├─ Clock synchronization accuracy: <100ps between nodes
├─ Frame duration: 1ms (1000 entanglement attempts per frame)
├─ Acknowledgment timeout: 10ms
├─ Maximum retransmissions: 3
├─ Handshake duration: <50ms for link establishment
└─ Entanglement generation rate: 10³-10⁵ pairs/second per link
```

4.2 Quantum Key Distribution Protocol (BB84-SAT)

```
Modified BB84 for Satellite Channels:
├─ Basis choice: {H,V} and {+45°,-45°}
├─ Pulse repetition: 100MHz
├─ Decoy states: 3 intensity levels (μ, ν, 0)
├─ Finite-key analysis: 10¹⁰ pulses per key generation
├─ Sifted key rate: >10kbps per satellite pass
├─ Final key rate: >1kbps after error correction/privacy amplification
├─ Quantum bit error rate (QBER): <5% threshold
├─ Secure distance: Up to 1200km (satellite to ground)
├─ Authentication: Wegman-Carter with 128-bit security
└─ Key management: Quantum key pool with 1TB storage

Security Parameters:
├─ Privacy amplification: Toeplitz hashing with 2-universal hash
├─ Error correction: Low-density parity check (LDPC) codes
├─ Verification: Random sampling of 20% of sifted key
├─ Authentication tag: 256 bits per message
├─ Key refresh: Every 10 minutes or 1GB of data
└─ Forward secrecy: Guaranteed by quantum mechanics
```

