```
Radiation:
├─ Total ionizing dose: 30krad (Si) over 10 years behind 3mm Al
├─ Single event effects:
│  ├─ LET threshold: 1 MeV·cm²/mg
│  ├─ SEU rate: <1 event/day for critical systems
│  └─ SEL protection: Current limiting, watchdog timers
├─ Proton fluence: 10¹¹ protons/cm² (>10MeV)
├─ Electron fluence: 10¹⁵ electrons/cm² (>1MeV)
└─ Mitigation: Radiation-hardened components, shielding, error correction

Thermal:
├─ External temperature range: -150°C to +150°C
├─ Payload operational: 20°C ± 0.1°C (controlled)
├─ Gradients: <1°C across optical bench
├─ Heat rejection: 150W peak through radiators
└─ Survival heaters: 50W capability for eclipse

Micrometeoroids and Debris:
├─ Probability of impact: <1% over 10 years for critical surfaces
├─ Protection: Whipple shields for vulnerable components
├─ Optical surfaces: Redundant apertures or protective covers
└─ Detection: Onboard sensors for impact detection
```

