9.0 INTERFACE SPECIFICATIONS

9.1 Quantum-Classical Interface

```
Quantum Processor Interface (QPI):
├─ Physical layer: Single-mode fiber, FC/APC connectors
├─ Wavelength: 1550nm ± 0.1nm
├─ Power level: -70dBm to -40dBm (single photon level)
├─ Polarization: Maintained or actively compensated
├─ Timing: Synchronized to 10ps accuracy
├─ Control signals: LVDS, 100MHz clock, trigger pulses
├─ Data interface: PCIe Gen4 x8 (16Gbps) or 100G Ethernet
├─ Protocol: Quantum Instrumentation Control Kit (QICK) or custom
└─ Software API: Qiskit Runtime, Cirq, or custom SDK

Classical Communication Channel:
├─ Purpose: Coordination, basis reconciliation, error correction
├─ Data rate: 10Mbps minimum per quantum link
├─ Latency: <100ms round-trip (satellite-ground)
├─ Protocol: TCP/IP with quantum extensions
├─ Authentication: Quantum-resistant algorithms (SPHINCS+, Falcon)
├─ Encryption: AES-256 or quantum key distributed
└─ Reliability: 99.999% packet delivery
```

