11.0 SECURITY SPECIFICATIONS

11.1 Quantum Security

```
Physical Layer Security:
├─ Quantum random number generation: >100Mbps true random
├─ Source monitoring: Continuous characterization of entanglement
├─ Detector monitoring: Real-time monitoring for Trojan-horse attacks
├─ Channel monitoring: Photon number statistics verification
├─ Time-of-flight checks: Detection of photon number splitting
└─ Beam attenuation monitoring: Detection of intercept-resend

Protocol Security:
├─ Authentication: Unconditionally secure with quantum keys
├─ Encryption: One-time pad with quantum-generated keys
├─ Key management: Distributed quantum key pool
├─ Intrusion detection: Quantum channel disturbance monitoring
├─ Forward secrecy: Guaranteed by quantum no-cloning
└─ Backward secrecy: Key erasure after use

Network Security:
├─ Quantum firewall: Bell state measurements for verification
├─ Quantum honeypots: Decoy entanglement sources
├─ Traffic analysis protection: Quantum superposition routing
├─ DDoS protection: Rate limiting at quantum level
└─ Access control: Quantum identity verification
```

11.2 Classical Security

```
Infrastructure Security:
├─ Physical security: Biometric access, surveillance, guards
├─ Network security: Firewalls, intrusion detection, air gaps
├─ Data security: Encryption at rest and in transit
├─ Application security: Code signing, vulnerability scanning
├─ Supply chain security: Trusted foundries, component verification
└─ Personnel security: Background checks, need-to-know access

Cryptographic Algorithms:
├─ Quantum-resistant: CRYSTALS-Kyber (key exchange)
├─ Quantum-resistant: CRYSTALS-Dilithium (signatures)
├─ Symmetric: AES-256 for bulk encryption
├─ Hash: SHA3-512 for integrity
└─ Randomness: Quantum random number generators
```

