```
Quantum Source Testing:
├─ Entanglement verification: Bell inequality violation >0.9
├─ Brightness stability: <5% variation over 24 hours
├─ Wavelength stability: <1pm drift over temperature range
├─ Polarization stability: <1° drift over 24 hours
├─ Vibration testing: Random vibration to 14.1Grms
├─ Thermal cycling: -40°C to +70°C, 100 cycles
├─ Radiation testing: 30krad total dose, heavy ion SEE
└─ Lifetime testing: 10⁹ photon pairs without degradation

Detector Testing:
├─ Detection efficiency: >85% at 1550nm
├─ Dark count: <10 counts/second at operating temperature
├─ Timing jitter: <50ps FWHM
├─ Afterpulse probability: <1%
├─ Count rate linearity: <5% deviation to 10⁷ counts/second
├─ Vibration sensitivity: <10% efficiency change
├─ Magnetic field sensitivity: <1% efficiency change at 1G
└─ Lifetime: >10¹² counts without degradation
```

13.2 System Testing

```
End-to-End Testing:
├─ Entanglement distribution: Ground-to-ground via test satellite
├─ Distance: 100km, 500km, 1000km progressively
├─ Rate measurement: At each distance with varying conditions
├─ Fidelity measurement: Quantum state tomography
├─ Day/night operation: Performance comparison
├─ Weather conditions: Clear, cloudy, light rain
├─ Mobility testing: Moving ground terminals
└─ Network testing: Multiple simultaneous links

Acceptance Testing:
├─ Factory acceptance: All specifications verified before shipment
├─ Site acceptance: Verified after installation at site
├─ On-orbit checkout: 30-day comprehensive test after launch
├─ Operational readiness: 7-day continuous operation test
├─ Performance verification: Quarterly comprehensive tests
└─ Annual recertification: Complete system retest
```

14.0 DEPLOYMENT SCHEDULE

14.1 Development Timeline

```
Phase 0: Technology Development (2024-2026)
├─ Q1 2024: Component prototypes (sources, detectors, memories)
├─ Q4 2024: Laboratory entanglement distribution (1km simulated)
├─ Q2 2025: Airborne demonstration (balloon to ground)
├─ Q4 2025: First space-qualified components
├─ Q2 2026: Complete satellite prototype
└─ Q4 2026: Ground station prototype

Phase 1: Pathfinder Mission (2027-2028)
├─ Q1 2027: Launch single demonstration satellite
├─ Q3 2027: First satellite-ground quantum link
├─ Q1 2028: Ground-to-ground via satellite (1000km)
├─ Q3 2028: First network protocols demonstration
└─ Q4 2028: Pathfinder mission report and lessons learned

Phase 2: Pilot Constellation (2029-2031)
├─ Q1 2029: Launch 3-satellite network
├─ Q3 2029: Continuous coverage demonstration
├─ Q1 2030: First applications (QKD, sensing)
├─ Q3 2030: Expand to 12 satellites
├─ Q1 2031: Regional network operational
└─ Q4 2031: Pilot phase complete, ready for full deployment

Phase 3: Global Deployment (2032-2036)
├─ 2032: 50 satellites launched, initial global coverage
├─ 2033: 150 satellites, continuous regional coverage
├─ 2034: 300 satellites, moderate global coverage
├─ 2035: 500 satellites, good global coverage
├─ 2036: 600 satellites, complete constellation
└─ 2037: Full operational capability declared
```

14.2 Ground Segment Deployment

```
Year 1 (2027): 3 primary ground stations (Chile, Canary Islands, Australia)
Year 2 (2028): +5 stations (Hawaii, South Africa, India, China, USA)
Year 3 (2029): +10 stations (global distribution)
Year 4 (2030): +20 stations (major population centers)
Year 5 (2031): +12 stations (complete 50 primary stations)
Year 6-10 (2032-2036): Deploy 200 metropolitan nodes
```

